HEADWORD: Palladic
<hw>Pal*la"dic</hw> <pr>(p⟦acr⟧l*l⟦amac⟧"d⟦icr⟧k <it>or</it>
p⟦acr⟧l*l⟦acr⟧d"⟦icr⟧k)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>Of,
pertaining to, or derived from, palladium; -- used specifically to
designate those compounds in which the element has a higher valence as
contrasted with <contr>palladious</contr> compounds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

